    {
      "first_name": "William Godfrey",
      "last_name": "Gregory",
      "born_year": 1834,
      "born_place": "Carrington, Nottinghamshire",
      "died_date": "13 December 1912",
      "died_year": 1912,
      "bio": "William Godfrey Gregory (b. c. 1834, Carrington, Nottinghamshire; d. 13 December 1912) was the son of William Gregory, who began his career as a coal miner but later established himself as a lace manufacturer in Nottingham. William Gregory senior retired from Gregory and Sons, lace manufacturers and cotton doublers in 1866, leaving William Godfrey in partnership with his brothers Isaiah and Hezekiah Gregory in W.G. and I. and H. Gregory. On 31 December 1875 the partnership between WG and Isaiah in Gregory Brothers was dissolved, leaving William Godfrey as sole owner of the business. His business, based at Canal Street, Nottingham, was variously named as William G. Gregory Ltd. and W.G. Gregory (of Nottingham) Ltd. The latter went into voluntary liquidation in 1926.\n\nWilliam Godfrey married Harriett Gregory (b. c.1835; d. 1903). He died on 13th December 1912, still resident at Clumber House, leaving an estate worth \u00a3128,859 net.",
